definition.value: A thiophene that is substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 4.
A member of the class of phytosterols that is 5beta-cholestane carrying a hydroxy substituent at the 3beta-position.
A 3beta-hydroxy steroid that is 5beta-androstane substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3beta and an oxo group at position 17. It is a metabolite of testosterone.
A member of the class of furans that is furan in which the hydrogens at positions 2 and 4 are replaced by methyl groups.
An enone that is pent-2-ene in which the two methylene hydrogens have been replaced by an oxo group.
